# Code Documentation Standards

## 1. JSDoc for Functions & Classes
Every function must include a JSDoc block defining its purpose, parameters, and return values.
- **Example:**
  ```javascript
  /**
   * Initializes the Braze WebSDK and sets up the user session.
   * @param {string} apiKey - The Braze API key from the dashboard.
   * @param {Object} options - Configuration options for initialization.
   * @returns {boolean} - Returns true if initialization was successful.
   */
  function initBraze(apiKey, options) { ... }
  ```
  
